-# AC-2(j) access recertification. Review each account's role, last login, and MFA status,
-# then confirm or revoke. Rows highlighted = privileged account WITHOUT MFA (a finding).
.row
  .col-md-12
    %h3 Access Review
    %p.text-muted
      Periodic recertification (AC-2(j)). PER TENANT - run once per subdomain to cover all staff.
    = link_to 'Export CSV', access_review_path(format: :csv), class: 'btn btn-default btn-sm'
.table-responsive
  %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
    %thead
      %tr
        %th Name
        %th Email
        %th Role
        %th Last Sign In
        %th Count
        %th MFA
        %th Passkeys
        %th Locked
        %th Disabled
        %th Created
    %tbody
      - @users.each do |u|
        %tr{ class: ('warning' if u.mfa_privileged? && !u.two_factor_enabled?) }
          %td= u.name
          %td= u.email
          %td= u.roles
          %td= u.last_sign_in_at&.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
          %td= u.sign_in_count
          %td
            - if u.two_factor_enabled?
              %span.label.label-success on
            - else
              %span.label.label-default off
          %td= u.webauthn_credentials.size
          %td= ('yes' if u.respond_to?(:access_locked?) && u.access_locked?)
          %td= ('yes' if u.disable?)
          %td= u.created_at&.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')

-# Phase 5.5 (AC-6) least-privilege SHADOW window. While config.x.enforce_least_privilege is OFF,
-# this lists -- per staff member + rule -- how often the narrowed ProgressNote/version rules WOULD
-# have denied access. Validation evidence to review BEFORE flipping the flag. Counts only, no records.
.row
  .col-md-12
    %h4 Least-Privilege Shadow Divergences
    %p.text-muted
      AC-6 shadow window (enforcement OFF). How often the narrowed rules WOULD have denied access, per staff member. Review before enabling enforcement.
- if @lp_shadow_summary.present?
  .table-responsive
    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
      %thead
        %tr
          %th User
          %th Rule
          %th Count
          %th Last Seen
      %tbody
        - @lp_shadow_summary.each do |row|
          %tr
            %td= row[:email]
            %td= row[:rule]
            %td= row[:count]
            %td= row[:last_seen]&.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
- else
  %p.text-muted No shadow divergences recorded yet.

-# Phase 5.6 (AC-3) authorization-cutover SHADOW window. While config.x.enforce_authorization is OFF, lists
-# -- per controller/action/role -- how often an action WOULD have failed the mandatory-authorization check
-# (would 403 once the flag is flipped). Review until only expected allowlist/authorized actions appear.
.row
  .col-md-12
    %h4 Authorization-Cutover Shadow (AC-3)
    %p.text-muted
      Global authorization cutover shadow window (enforcement OFF). Actions that WOULD fail the mandatory authorization check, by controller/action/role. Review before flipping enforce_authorization.
- if @authz_shadow_summary.present?
  .table-responsive
    %table.table.table-striped.table-condensed
      %thead
        %tr
          %th Controller
          %th Action
          %th Role
          %th Count
          %th Last Seen
      %tbody
        - @authz_shadow_summary.each do |row|
          %tr
            %td= row[:controller]
            %td= row[:action]
            %td= row[:role]
            %td= row[:count]
            %td= row[:last_seen]&.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
- else
  %p.text-muted No authorization-cutover divergences recorded yet.
